    <!--
    Custom XFTL strings.
    All string IDs must be prefixed with 'xftl_' to make their origin obvious in code
    Try to use vanilla strings where possible (eg for ok/cancel) as they're already translated.
    -->

    <text name="xftl_edit_ship">EDIT SHIP</text>
    <text name="xftl_clear_edit_ship">DISCARD CHANGES</text>

    <text name="xftl_select_datafile_title">Select an FTL datafile</text>
    <text name="xftl_select_datafile_desc">
        Project Wormhole uses the original game assets, which requires a copy of the original game.
        If you have installed FTL via the Steam or Epic Games storefronts, it should be auto-detected.

        Otherwise, run FTL and it will also be auto-detected.

        If neither of the above work, you'll have to set the path to ftl.dat manually.
        To do this, put the full OS path to FTL's data/ftl.dat file in:
        \1
    </text>
    <text name="xftl_select_datafile_not_found">No auto-detected FTL installations</text>

